records.addlTxt:
11:50 AM Defendant Kayla Star Gengler in court, in custody.  Attorney Michael Charles Hoffman in court for Kayla Star Gengler.  Attorney Angela M Wilson in court for State of Wisconsin. State recites agreement that defendant to plead to Count 3. For Count 3, 4 years prison fashioned as 2 years initial confinement and 2 years extended supervision imposed and stayed for 3 years probation. Probation concurrent with MN probation case but if revoked, consecutive prison time with MN case. Conditions of probation include serve 62 days with credit for 62 days served, pay a $20 fine plus costs and comply with all programming as deemed necessary by the DOC. Defendant would be eligible for both substance abuse programming and challenge incarceration program. Defendant pleads guilty to Count 3. Counts 1 and 2 are to be dismissed. Attorney Hoffman stipulates to a factual basis. Court accepts the Defendant's plea and finds that the Defendant's plea has been freely, voluntarily and intelligently made. The Defendant understands all the rights she is waiving by her plea. The Defendant is found guilty and Judgment of Conviction is entered.

Court orders for Count 3, 4 years prison fashioned as 2 years initial confinement and 2 years extended supervision imposed and stayed for 3 years probation. Probation concurrent with MN probation case but if revoked, consecutive prison time with MN case. Conditions of probation include serve 62 days with credit for 62 days served, pay a $20 fine plus costs and comply with all programming as deemed necessary by the DOC. Defendant eligible for both substance abuse programming and challenge incarceration program. Count 2 and 3 are dismissed.
Plea/sentencing hearing on June 29, 2022 at 11:45 am.

11:33 AM Defendant Kayla Star Gengler appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Michael Charles Hoffman in court for Kayla Star Gengler.  Attorney Angela M Wilson in court for State of Wisconsin. Court calls case. Attorney receives information, waives reading, pleads not guilty. Case may be resolved.  Asks for status.
Status conference scheduled for July 22, 2022 at 11:30 am.

2:15 PM Defendant Kayla Star Gengler appeared by video.  Attorney Michael Charles Hoffman in court for Kayla Star Gengler.  Attorney Angela M Wilson in court for State of Wisconsin. Court calls case. Attorney Hoffman argues bail set on May 4th, unable to post, indigent. Lifelong resident of Superior. Could come up with $700. 
State argues very extensive history of failures to appear, mostly in Minnesota, 37 dates with multiple failures to appear. These are felony matters. On probation in Minnesota. Believes the $5000 is appropriate.
Attorney Hoffman has nothing additional to add.
Court indicates 39 failures to appear is the most he's ever heard so far. Denies motion. Bail and conditions to continue.
Defendant's Notice of Motion and Motion for Bail Modification

8:50 AM Prosecuting attorney Mark Adam Fruehauf in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Kayla Star Gengler in court, in custody.  Attorney Michael Charles Hoffman in court for Kayla Star Gengler. 
Att Hoffman- client will waive prelim
Court finds waiver is voluntary, finds probable cause for bind over. Sets date
Arraignment scheduled for June 10, 2022 at 11:30 am.
